Text: Pardon me.
We've received confirmation.

Gettan, the MCA's de facto leader, is without a doubt
connected to the Cult.

His plan was to introduce counterfeit bills into
circulation and cause a credit crisis to bring down
Mitsugoshi.

They're willing to go down in flames... They saw
Mitsugoshi as a threat, separate from the Shadow
Garden...

While we were caught up in our economic war, Master
Shadow picked up on this and acted independently...
No wonder he abandoned us...
*gasp*
He picked up...on the counterfeits...?

The Cult's plan was to introduce counterfeits into
circulation.
Y-Yes, but...
The Cult hasn't actually...
...started introducing counterfeits yet.
*gasp*

B-But there are counterfeits currently in
circulation...

Wait, you mean the one circulating those counterfeits
is...
Exactly.

Shadow orchestrated this. He changed his name,
cut ties with us, and circulated the counterfeit
bills before the Cult could.
...His intention is—
Lady Alpha!

Beta comes barreling into the room without so much
as a knock. She's holding a sheet of paper in her hand.
Look at this!

We've decoded the encrypted message Master Shadow
left us!
Eta deciphered the message...!

Alpha takes the document from Beta and begins
reading the text.
Lady Alpha...?
He...
He didn't abandon us after all...!
*gasp*
"Sorry...but I have to betray you all."
"To initiate a certain plan, I abandoned my old names,"

"and teamed up with an accomplice to produce
counterfeit money."

"We're squirreling away all the money in the old
facility we saved my sister from back when we
were kids."

"I know you all might resent me for this, but I
believe this choice..."
"...was for the best."
Master Shadow set this all up...for us.
So he's been looking at the bigger picture.

He saw through it all and made the best possible
choice... An act truly befitting the man.

He realized the Cult's plan sooner than anyone else.
Then he used it against them.

By making his own counterfeits before the Cult could
act, he was able to amass a shocking amount of
capital.

With that gold, Mitsugoshi will be able to survive
the credit crisis. When that happens, the Cult will
have lost the MCA. They'll be the sole losers.

The Cult picked a fight with the wrong man. Master
Shadow's understanding of money creation was what
made his plan possible.

He understood how dangerous a credit crisis could be,
and he came up with a bold, efficient method of
raising funds... A class act all around.

And that explains why he had to hide his identity,
too—to remove the link between him and us. Thus,
he's hiding that there's a connection between the
counterfeits, Mitsugoshi, and the Shadow Garden.

He even went so far as to set up his factory
somewhere we were familiar with, then told
us where the vault was.

To fool your enemies, first fool your friends...
That's what he was doing all along.
All we have to do is pick up the gold.

A perfect plan formed on a foundation of subtlety and
precise calculation... That's Master Shadow for you.
"Once all this is over,"
"you'll realize this was for the best..."
It's just like he told me.
But...what about Delta?
Don't worry.
Huh...?
Delta.
Ha-ruff...
Delta!
Seriously! You had us worried!

Oh‑woof... I was...on a confidential secret mission,
see... So...
We know. Master Shadow had a job for you, right?

There was a black Juggler, and I...! Oh, it's a
confidential secret mission, so I can't tell you...
Come on now, Delta, speak properly.

Calling it a "confidential secret mission" is
redundant.
B‑But that's what Boss man said...!
Don't be silly, of course he didn't.
Ha-ruff...
Still, I'm so glad you're okay...
Oh-woof?
